	<div class="blogbody">
	
	<a name="001185"></a>
	<h3 class="title">Final writing assignment</h3>
	
	<p>For the final writing assignment, you will have to write a longer paper (between 8-10 pages) on a topic of your choice about the social implications of computing. <i>Your paper should argue for a position.</i> Although you have a wide choice of topics, you will have to narrow your focus to something that is appropriate for the scope of an 8-10 page paper. For example, if you decide to write about "censorship," you should explore a particular aspect concerning censorship; do not cram loosely related subtopics (parental control, hate speech, authoritarian governmental censorship) all into one paper. At the same time, you should make sure that your topic is complex enough that you'd have interesting materials to discuss for 8-10 pages. 

<p>By the end of November, you should have already defined the thesis of your paper; you should also have some ideas about how you will structure your paper. The final draft of your paper is due by noon, December 12th. <b>Please email your paper to me as well as to the TA.</b>

<p>If you need some suggestions to get started, take a look at this <a href="http://www-rohan.sdsu.edu/faculty/giftfire/papertopics">website</a> for a similar class. It contains an extensive list of potential paper topics, and some of them seem quite interesting. <b>Note:</b> although this list is a good starting point for brain-storming, some of the suggested outlines are not well suited for a position paper. So if you wish to pursue one of these suggested topics, you will still have to further refine it into a workable thesis. 

	
	
	
