	<div class="blogbody">
	
	<a name="001129"></a>
	<h3 class="title">Introduction</h3>
	
	<p><p>Welcome to <i>Social Implications of Computing</i>. Please read the course policies page (follow the link on the side panel).  By September 2nd, you should have turned in a signed statement acknowledging that you have read and understood the course policies.</p>

<p><h3>First reading assignment</h3></p>

<p><p>Please read the following article:</p>

<blockquote>
<p>Tierney, John <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/26/science/26tier.html?8dpc">Technology That Outthinks Us: A Partner or a Master?</a> New York Times, August 25, 2008.
</blockquote>

<p><p>You should then write a short "reading reaction" to this article and post it as a comment to this entry.  The reaction is due by noon 8/28 (this Thursday).</p>
	
	
	
	<div class="posted">Posted by hwa at <a href="https://www.cs.pitt.edu/~hwa/cs1590/archives/001129.html">01:56 PM</a>
		| <a href="https://blogs.cs.pitt.edu/mt-comments.cgi?entry_id=1129" onclick="OpenComments(this.href); return false">Comments (16)</a>
	
	
